<TITLE> ACC sues Justice Fazlul Haque </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 13 (bdnews24.com)The Anticorruption Commission Sunday filed a case against former caretaker government adviser Fazlul Haque on charges of amassing money by unfair means and concealing information about wealth, a police officer said. ACC assistant director Mohammad Ibrahim filed the case with Ramna Police Station, sub-inspector Jahangir Alam of Ramna Police Station told bdnews24.com. According to case details, the former judge earned Tk 97.37 lakh by unfair means. The ACC had earlier carried out an investigation into the wealth of Justice Haque. According to the investigation report, the ACC also found Tk 14 crore in the bank accounts of Haque's son Dr Afzal Hossain Raj, son-in-law Tariqur Rahman Prince and son's friends. ACC did not find any source of the money. In his wealth statement submitted to the ACC, Justice Haque said he owned property worth Tk 1.25 crore. bdnews24.
